In this article, President is asked why he visited a border state without actually visiting the border. He responds by saying that there is a more important thing happening, which is a new investment in the state. The President is then asked about power outages in North Carolina, and he says that they don't yet know who is behind it and that he is looking into it. He is also asked about Catholic bishops objecting to the Respect for Marriage Act, to which he simply says that he disagrees. Finally, the President mentions that he is looking forward to the Africa Summit.